    label "section_652_subsection_b_item_4"
    class_name "item"
    text "(4) the term &#8220;Upper Mississippi River Basin Association&#8221; means an association of the States of Illinois, Iowa, Minnesota, Missouri, and Wisconsin, formed for the purposes of cooperative effort and united assistance in the comprehensive planning for the use, protection, growth, and development of the Upper Mississippi River System."
  ]
