    label "section_1362"
    class_name "section"
    text "&#167;1362. Definitions"
  ]
  node [
    id 4026
    label "section_1362_item_1"
    class_name "item"
    text "(1) The term &#8220;State water pollution control agency&#8221; means the State agency designated by the Governor having responsibility for enforcing State laws relating to the abatement of pollution."
  ]
  node [
    id 4027
    label "section_1362_item_2"
    class_name "item"
    text "(2) The term &#8220;interstate agency&#8221; means an agency of two or more States established by or pursuant to an agreement or compact approved by the Congress, or any other agency of two or more States, having substantial powers or duties pertaining to the control of pollution as determined and approved by the Administrator."
  ]
  node [
    id 4028
    label "section_1362_item_3"
    class_name "item"
    text "(3) The term &#8220;State&#8221; means a State, the District of Columbia, the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico, the Virgin Islands, Guam, American Samoa, the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands, and the Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands."
  ]
  node [
    id 4029
    label "section_1362_item_4"
    class_name "item"
    text "(4) The term &#8220;municipality&#8221; means a city, town, borough, county, parish, district, association, or other public body created by or pursuant to State law and having jurisdiction over disposal of sewage, industrial wastes, or other wastes, or an Indian tribe or an authorized Indian tribal organization, or a designated and approved management agency under section 1288 of this title."
  ]
  node [
    id 4030
    label "section_1362_item_5"
    class_name "item"
    text "(5) The term &#8220;person&#8221; means an individual, corporation, partnership, association, State, municipality, commission, or political subdivision of a State, or any interstate body."
  ]
  node [
    id 4031
    label "section_1362_item_6"
    class_name "item"
    text "(6) The term &#8220;pollutant&#8221; means dredged spoil, solid waste, incinerator residue, sewage, garbage, sewage sludge, munitions, chemical wastes, biological materials, radioactive materials, heat, wrecked or discarded equipment, rock, sand, cellar dirt and industrial, municipal, and agricultural waste discharged into water. This term does not mean (A) &#8220;sewage from vessels&#8221; within the meaning of section 1322 of this title; or (B) water, gas, or other material which is injected into a well to facilitate production of oil or gas, or water derived in association with oil or gas production and disposed of in a well, if the well used either to facilitate production or for disposal purposes is approved by authority of the State in which the well is located, and if such State determines that such injection or disposal will not result in the degradation of ground or surface water resources."
  ]
  node [
    id 4032
    label "section_1362_item_7"
    class_name "item"
    text "(7) The term &#8220;navigable waters&#8221; means the waters of the United States, including the territorial seas."
  ]
  node [
    id 4033
    label "section_1362_item_8"
    class_name "item"
    text "(8) The term &#8220;territorial seas&#8221; means the belt of the seas measured from the line of ordinary low water along that portion of the coast which is in direct contact with the open sea and the line marking the seaward limit of inland waters, and extending seaward a distance of three miles."
  ]
  node [
    id 4034
    label "section_1362_item_9"
    class_name "item"
    text "(9) The term &#8220;contiguous zone&#8221; means the entire zone established or to be established by the United States under article 24 of the Convention of the Territorial Sea and the Contiguous Zone."
  ]
  node [
    id 4035
    label "section_1362_item_10"
    class_name "item"
    text "(10) The term &#8220;ocean&#8221; means any portion of the high seas beyond the contiguous zone."
  ]
  node [
    id 4036
    label "section_1362_item_11"
    class_name "item"
    text "(11) The term &#8220;effluent limitation&#8221; means any restriction established by a State or the Administrator on quantities, rates, and concentrations of chemical, physical, biological, and other constituents which are discharged from point sources into navigable waters, the waters of the contiguous zone, or the ocean, including schedules of compliance."
  ]
  node [
    id 4037
    label "section_1362_item_12"
    class_name "item"
    text "(12) The term &#8220;discharge of a pollutant&#8221; and the term &#8220;discharge of pollutants&#8221; each means (A) any addition of any pollutant to navigable waters from any point source, (B) any addition of any pollutant to the waters of the contiguous zone or the ocean from any point source other than a vessel or other floating craft."
  ]
  node [
    id 4038
    label "section_1362_item_13"
    class_name "item"
    text "(13) The term &#8220;toxic pollutant&#8221; means those pollutants, or combinations of pollutants, including disease-causing agents, which after discharge and upon exposure, ingestion, inhalation or assimilation into any organism, either directly from the environment or indirectly by ingestion through food chains, will, on the basis of information available to the Administrator, cause death, disease, behavioral abnormalities, cancer, genetic mutations, physiological malfunctions (including malfunctions in reproduction) or physical deformations, in such organisms or their offspring."
  ]
  node [
    id 4039
    label "section_1362_item_14"
    class_name "item"
    text "(14) The term &#8220;point source&#8221; means any discernible, confined and discrete conveyance, including but not limited to any pipe, ditch, channel, tunnel, conduit, well, discrete fissure, container, rolling stock, concentrated animal feeding operation, or vessel or other floating craft, from which pollutants are or may be discharged. This term does not include agricultural stormwater discharges and return flows from irrigated agriculture."
  ]
  node [
    id 4040
